s. And Gabrielle was sick. With all this going on and more obviously waiting for her back in Ephesus, Ari had to make a decision. Though she had known the answer for a while now, she had been avoiding it. But no more. Ari wouldn't be returning to fight in the war.<br>
<br>
She sighed and looked from Amazon to Amazon and couldn't help but wondered who she wouldn't be seeing again. The Saurians were strong, from what she could tell, and would not be easily defeated. Lives would be lost-both those of warriors and those of innocents, not fighting in the war.<br>
<br>
On that thought, her gaze drifted to Crystal and she walked over to her. &quot;I'm not coming back,&quot; She admitted and took a necklace off her head, then put it over Crystal's. &quot;Gabrielle gave this to me for protection. I want to give it to you...and the baby.&quot; She smiled softly and hugged her friend. The word friend was more of an understatement, too. More like sister.<br>
<br>
